g.text: Many numerical measures may be applied for evaluating the performances of our
clustering methods. Broadly speaking, they can be external, internal and relative
Cohesion measures how related are the data points inside a cluster
Separation measures how well-separated is a cluster from the others
It combines cohesion and separation and it is defined for a point Pi
average dissimilarity of Pi with all other objects
minimum between the average dissimilarity of Pi with
respect to all the other clusters' elements
the silhouette coefficient varies from -1 to 1 and
it means Ai and Bi are high, hence
there is a nice cohesion and separation
